      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Urban streetwear today is all about blending high fashion with street culture, often featuring oversized silhouettes, bold prints, and a mix of luxury and thrifted items. It's heavily influenced by African American and Latino communities, so make sure to incorporate elements like bold patterns, vibrant colors, and oversized logos. Don't shy away from using cultural symbols and motifs, but always ensure they're used in a way that feels authentic and not just a superficial nod to the culture. Embrace the diversity of urban life, but remember that the true essence of streetwear lies in its ability to represent the struggles and triumphs of marginalized communities.",
